# Coding Standards

- Keep diffs focused and task-scoped; avoid opportunistic refactors.
- Preserve strict TypeScript compatibility and shared contract reuse.
- Validate API inputs with Zod before side effects.
- Keep search pipeline guarantees intact:
  - `Promise.allSettled` fan-out
  - per-adapter failure isolation
  - retry/rate-limit wrappers
  - explicit search status transitions
- Never commit secrets or print credential values in logs.
- Treat Prisma writes to related entities as transactional when possible.
- Use `maisonDeux` for user-facing naming and copy.

## Required Verification

- Backend changes: `npm run typecheck -w @luxefinder/api`
- Mobile changes: `npm run typecheck -w @luxefinder/mobile`
- Behavior changes in API/adapters/pipeline: `npm run test -w @luxefinder/api`
- Deployment changes: verify live `200` at `maisondeux.vip` and `www.maisondeux.vip`
